IAM 


(IAM) Identity and access management 


Users and groups:  
*users don’t have to belong to a group * 
*users can belong to multiple groups*
*groups don’t contain other groups *

IAM root user -> the first user created that is a “super user” that has access to everything in AWS - can change and modify 
User -> created by the root user and the permissions assigned ti it like read only / custom polices 
Group -> collection of IAM users that have policies and permissions allocated to them by the root user -> efficient way to manage many users 

Practical steps   
- Adding users names and passwords - able to send them an email 
- Adding users to groups 
- Back to IAM dashboard - top right - Sign-in URL for IAM users in this account



Policies & permissions:     You attach policies → Policies contain permissions

Policy (JSON documents) ->  is a set of rules that define what actions are allowed/denied in AWS -> read only access  
- Managed Policy → Separate, reusable policy
- Inline Policy → Built directly inside one IAM identity
- Example -> user is created , added to group A with policy 1 and has an inline policy attached policy 2 = policy 1+ policy 2

Permission -> is the practical application of a policy when it is applied to a user/ group -> user can only read the document  
- Apply least privilege for best practice

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",   - policy language version 
  "Id": "PolicyIdentifier",       - identifier for policy (optional) 
  "Statement": [                        - one/more individual statements ( required ) 
    {
      "Sid": "StatementIdentifier",    - an identifier for the statement ( optional ) 
      "Effect": "Allow",                           - whether the statement allows/deny access ( Allow/deny )
      "Principal": {                                    
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:user/Hassan" -             ]- account/user/role this policy applies to 
      },
      "Condition": {                                                 ]- conditions for which this policy will apply 
        "IpAddress": {
          "aws:SourceIp": "203.0.113.0/24"
        }
      },
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",                    - list of Actions this policy will deny/allow 
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket/*"       - list of resources to which the actions applied to 
    }
  ]
}

